value.value: A specialized epithelial cell that is capable of synthesizing and secreting certain biomolecules.
An epithelial cell of the integument (the outer layer of an organism).
Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.
The anatomical structure which is part of the hemolymph vascular system and consists of a vascular wall and a vascular lumen.
A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.
An open tracheal system is a respiratory system, a branched network of epithelial tubes that supplies oxygen to target tissues via spiracles.
